BWithout%20a%20doubt%2C%20we%20are%20a%20little%20scared%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tyler%20Pinson%2C%20CEO%20of%20Navarre%20Corporation%2C%20a%20company%20that%20provides%20non-emergency%20medical%20transportation%20to%20VA%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPinson%20said%20there's%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20contracting%20industry%20and%20he's%20curious%20about%20where%20federal%20cuts%20will%20be%20directed.%20However%2C%20he%20said%20he%20thinks%20%26quot%3Bservices%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20interrupted%26quot%3B%20or%20eliminated%2C%20and%20past%20administrations%20haven't%20impacted%20demand%20for%20Navarre's%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20spoke%20to%20more%20than%20half%20a%20dozen%20business%20owners%20and%20consultants%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-tips-government-contracting-jobs-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20contracting%3C%2Fa%3E%20space%20about%20how%20they%20feel%20DOGE%20could%20impact%20their%20work.%20Many%20of%20them%20said%20they%20see%20it%20as%20an%20opportunity%2C%20even%20if%20it%20comes%20with%20uncertainties%20and%20challenges%2C%20such%20as%20potentially%20lower%20contract%20amounts%20or%20more%20ambitious%20deadlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20envision%20a%20lot%20more%20contracts%20coming%20out%20to%20outsource%20to%20government%20contractors%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Derek%20Hoyt%2C%20CEO%20of%20government%20contracting%20platform%20GovSignals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeniece%20Peterson%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20federal%20market%20analysis%20at%20Deltek%2C%20which%20provides%20enterprise%20software%20for%20government%20contracting%20and%20other%20project-based%20businesses%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20if%20federal%20workforce%20reductions%20occur%20and%20specialized%20expertise%20is%20still%20required%2C%20it%20could%20create%20opportunities%20for%20other%20contractors.%20She%20said%20areas%20of%20opportunity%20depend%20on%20the%20particular%20market%20government%20contractors%20are%20working%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20contractors%20working%20in%20federal%20offices%20might%20face%20challenges%20from%20agency%20budget%20cuts%20or%20return-to-office%20mandates.%20However%2C%20Peterson%20said%20the%20return-to-office%20mandates%20could%20also%20result%20in%20additional%20IT%2C%20maintenance%2C%20catering%2C%20and%20janitorial%20service%20contracts%20awarded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20there's%20gaps%20in%20the%20federal%20workforce%2C%20that%20can%20be%20an%20opportunity%20for%20contracts%2C%26quot%3B%20Peterson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELimits%20on%20how%20much%20federal%20agencies%20can%20rely%20on%20outside%20contracts%20have%20already%20emerged%20as%20more%20details%20about%20President%20Trump's%20federal%20hiring%20freeze%20are%20distributed.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-federal-worker-job-offers-revoked-memo-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20memo%20sent%20to%20the%20heads%20of%20executive%20departments%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20federal%20agencies%20on%20Monday%20said%20that%20contractors%20can't%20be%20hired%20to%20take%20on%20the%20work%20that%20would%20have%20normally%20been%20filled%20by%20the%20roles%20in%20impacted%20job%20listings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAgencies%20shall%20not%20acquire%20by%20contract%20with%20a%20commercial%20vendor%20services%20that%20are%20substantially%20similar%20to%20those%20that%20would%20have%20been%20provided%20by%20a%20Federal%20civilian%20in%20a%20vacancy%20covered%20by%20the%20%5Bpresidential%20memorandum%5D%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20memo%20said%20in%20reference%20to%20Trump's%20executive%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoyt%20said%20the%20directive%20ensures%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20prospective%20federal%20civilian%20hire%20could%20not%20be%20brought%20in%20as%20a%20contractor%26quot%3B%20to%20fulfill%20the%20original%20role.%20Peterson%20said%20that%20the%20instruction%20%26quot%3Bmay%20not%20make%20much%20difference%26quot%3B%20since%20contracts%20%26quot%3Bto%20replace%20certain%20functions%20could%20take%20longer%20to%20put%20into%20place%26quot%3B%20than%20the%20length%20of%20the%20current%20hiring%20freeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESymon%C3%A9%20Berry%2C%20a%20tech%20worker%20in%20government%20contracting%2C%20said%20she%20doesn't%20think%20federal%20cuts%20will%20happen%20%26quot%3Bin%20one%20fell%20swoop%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20even%20if%20there%20are%20some%20reductions%2C%20there%20will%20always%20be%20%26quot%3Bwork%20to%20be%20done%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20government%20contracting.%20She%20said%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20modernizing%20technology%20or%20making%20upgrades%2C%20tasks%20in%20line%20with%20DOGE's%20new%20mandate%2C%20government%20contractors%20are%20often%20hired%20to%20do%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238ef0343-0ace-4eb2-bc38-5d67b4e4fd75%5C%22%3EA%20more%20efficient%20government%20could%20remove%20a%20'major%20pain%20point'%20for%20contractors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERich%20Weber%2C%20a%20partner%20for%20advisory%20firm%20Moss%20Adams%2C%20which%20works%20with%20government%20contractors%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20interview%20ahead%20of%20Trump's%20inauguration%20that%20there%20will%20likely%20be%20a%20push%20for%20efficiency%20that%20begins%20with%20federal%20workers%20and%20trickles%20down%20to%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdaptability%20will%20become%20%26quot%3Bcritically%20important%26quot%3B%20for%20government%20contractors%20as%20will%20being%20able%20to%20expand%20into%20needed%20areas%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoyt%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20platform%20that%20helps%20clients%20win%20government%20contracts%2C%20said%20DOGE's%20push%20for%20operational%20efficiency%20could%20accelerate%20the%20contract%20award%20process%2C%20helping%20to%20remove%20%26quot%3Ba%20major%20pain%20point%20for%20our%20clients.%26quot%3B%20Speedier%20processes%20could%20also%20open%20up%20opportunities%20for%20smaller%20businesses%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoyt%20said%20that%20with%20the%20current%20system%20in%20place%2C%20it%20can%20take%20up%20to%2018%20months%20to%20win%20a%20contract%2C%20which%20could%20create%20national%20security%20risks%20in%20situations%20where%20agencies%20can't%20get%20access%20to%20what%20they%20need%20fast%20enough.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20extensive%20processes%2C%20rules%2C%20and%20regulations%20surrounding%20government%20funding%20awards%20often%20lead%20to%20lengthy%20timelines%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20many%20procurement%20opportunities%20that%20can%20arise%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20almost%2020%20years%20I've%20seen%20the%20compliance%20around%20the%20entire%20contracts%20life%20cycle%20kind%20of%20grow%20into%20this%20massive%20mountain%20of%20paperwork%20and%20documentation%20and%20bureaucracy%2C%26quot%3B%20Weber%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeber%20said%20DOGE%20could%20help%20simplify%20procurement%20procedures%2C%20speed%20up%20project%20initiation%2C%20and%20standardize%20requirements%20across%20agencies.%20He%20also%20said%20%26quot%3Baccelerated%20funding%20allocations%26quot%3B%20could%20%26quot%3Bimprove%20cash%20flow%2C%26quot%3B%20especially%20for%20small%20business%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3bbe4f9-8245-47f7-a01e-624aa0dc5386%5C%22%3EHigher%20standards%2C%20increased%20competition%2C%20and%20doing%20more%20with%20less%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERipple%20effects%20from%20DOGE%20could%20work%20their%20way%20to%20government%20contractors%20in%20the%20form%20of%20smaller%20federal%20budgets%20to%20fund%20contract%20work%20and%20pressure%20to%20fulfill%20contracts%20for%20less%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVivek%20Ramaswamy%2C%20who%20was%20co-leading%20DOGE%20with%20Elon%20Musk%20before%20backing%20out%20ahead%20of%20an%20expected%20run%20for%20Ohio%20governor%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxbusiness.com%2Fpolitics%2Framaswamy-says-some-federal-agencies-deleted-outright-doge-mass-reductions-tap%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20anticipates%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20cuts%20among%20federal%20contractors%20and%20others%20who%20are%20over-billing%20the%20government.%26quot%3B%20The%20US%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20posted%20in%20June%202024%20that%20the%20federal%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fblog%2Fsnapshot-government-wide-contracting-fy-2023-interactive-dashboard%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThese%2520contracts%2520are%2520used%2520to%2C2022%2520after%2520adjusting%2520for%2520inflation.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommitted%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20%24759%20billion%20in%20contracts%20in%20the%202023%20fiscal%20year%2C%20a%20roughly%20%2433%20billion%20year-over-year%20increase%20when%20adjusting%20for%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeber%20said%20it's%20possible%20that%20the%20government%20could%20place%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20scrutiny%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20bidding%20phase%20of%20contracts.%20He%20also%20said%20there%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Bstricter%20evaluation%20criteria%26quot%3B%20on%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20would%20be%20the%20whole%20idea%20behind%20the%20agency%2C%26quot%3B%20Weber%20said%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20bring%20up%20the%20quality%20and%20efficiency%20of%20government%20projects.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeber%20said%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-tech-contractor-job-overseas-travel-pay-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20efficiency%20will%20likely%20become%20a%20higher%20priority%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20delivering%20results%20under%20budget%20and%20ahead%20of%20schedule%20will%20become%20increasingly%20important.%20He%20added%20that%20there's%20a%20high%20potential%20that%20the%20number%20of%20contracts%20awarded%20could%20decrease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20say%20the%20overall%20budget%20decreases%2C%20then%20each%20individual%20line%20item%20may%20decrease%20and%20then%20you're%20go